{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=ic|亼|皀|t1=mouth|t2=a bowl of rice on a stand}}. In the modern form, the bowl of rice has corrupted into the similar but unrelated {{m-lite|zh|sc=Hani|良}} or {{m-lite|zh|sc=Hani|艮}}. The variant form {{m-lite|zh|sc=Hani|𠊊}} preserves the original composition.

[[w:Shuowen Jiezi|''Shuowen'']] interprets the {{och-l|*亼}} as a phonetic component.

